flowRoot.flowPara: Flathub is a growing collection of apps which can be easily installed on any Linux distribution. Browse from your app center or the command line.

flowPara.flowSpan: Make sure to follow the setup guide before installing.
See the command line tutorial for more information on managing Flatpak applications from the command line.

flowRoot.flowPara: There's no reason not to use a .flatpakref from the command line. The command is more straightforward without the file reference, and it teaches people the "correct way".
Each featured app has a short, informative descrption, which we'll probably have to write ourselves.
Flathub contains 162 apps (and counting!) These are some of them.
Flathub aims to be the central place to get and distribute apps for Linux. It is powered by Flatpak, which allows the Flathub apps to run on almost any Linux distribution.
If you are a Linux user, you can use Flathub to gain access to a growing collection of Flatpak applications.

App developers can submit their applications to be distributed to Flathub's growing user base, thus providing a single gateway to the entire Linux desktop ecosystem. For more information, see our guide.

At the moment, applications must either be open source or be available as a third party download. However, if you are a proprietary app developer and are interested in using Flathub, we would love to talk to you.
Security or legal issues can be reported to the Flathub maintainers.
Flathub is an attempt to transform the Linux desktop ecosystem for the better, and we need your help. If you can write, create websites, administer servers or write code, we would love your help.
Everything we do happens in the open.
